The Inspector-General of Police, IGP Usman Alkali Baba, has ordered immediate deployment of additional operational assets to complement officers and men attached to Operation Restore Peace in the South East.
This, according to the IG is to stem the rising tide of attacks on police officers and facilities.
IGP Usman Alkali Baba who disclosed this in a statement warned that attacks on police officers in the line of duty would no longer be tolerated
The Inspector-General of Police, IGP Usman Alkali Baba, condemned the recent spate of attacks on Police officers, facilities, and other police operational assets around the nation, particularly in the South East where there have been attacks on police stations, and ruthless murder of police officers in the line of duty to protect the citizenry, as well as the destruction of critical national infrastructures.
READ ALSO: IGP Usman Alkali Baba and the mark of effective leadership.
The statement added that the IGP ordered the “immediate deployment of additional operational assets to complement officers and men attached to Operation Restore Peace in the South East, and other launched operations, with the aim of flushing out criminal elements who hide under the guise of aggrieved citizens to perpetrate criminal acts.
“Attacks on police officers in the line of duty would no longer be tolerated under whatever guise, as the Force holds the lives of its personnel sacrosanct, and such unwarranted attacks would be strictly treated in accordance with extant laws.”
He also added that the Police is committed to the protection of lives and property while stressing that it is vital to respect the lives and fundamental rights of police officers and other security operatives, in order to enable them advance their sacred mandate of serving and protecting the citizens better.
There have been increased attacks on Government facilities in the region, as INEC officials were recently attacked conducting an election registration exercise.
